  "text": "In addition to the style of faulting factor, the differences in hanging wall versus footwall ground motions are accounted for in the [CITATION_1] attenuation relation by a hanging wall effect term. In order to distinguish between an observation recorded on the hanging wall or footwall of the event, a hanging wall classification is assigned to each observation (HW in Table 3 ), where HW ‫ס‬ 0 for footwall and HW ‫ס‬ 1 for hanging wall. Note that the definition of hanging wall and footwall in this case is different from the traditional geological definition. Sites that are off the ends of the fault or beyond the surface projection of the fault plane are considered footwall sites [CITATION_2] .",
